=head1 DESCRIPTION

High-level information about the managed rule group that your own rule
group is copied from. You can use the the metadata to track version
updates made to the originating rule group. You can retrieve all
objects for a rule group by calling DescribeRuleGroup
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/network-firewall/latest/APIReference/API_DescribeRuleGroup.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 SourceArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the rule group that your own rule
group is copied from.


=head2 SourceUpdateToken => Str

The update token of the Amazon Web Services managed rule group that
your own rule group is copied from. To determine the update token for
the managed rule group, call DescribeRuleGroup
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/network-firewall/latest/APIReference/API_DescribeRuleGroup.html#networkfirewall-DescribeRuleGroup-response-UpdateToken).



